Organizational anthropology. Mapping cultural patterns. Social practices. Ethnographic thinking. Challenges in studying one's own culture. Professional communities. Resistance to change. Communication networks. Argument as a tool. Leading meetings and moderating discussions. Co-creation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to discuss human-centered approach to change management in organizations and to give students some tools to practice this approach.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows what is organizational anthropology, organizational culture and understand how this knowledge can be useful for anyone inducing change at organizations; 2) knows how to analyze cultural and social aspects impacting change processes;  3) is able to use some basic anthropological methods as tools for change manager; 4) analyze reasons for resistance to change, have tools to deal with resistance; 5) knows how to design communications related to change;  6) has skills for co-creation and argumented leadership.
